The police in Edo state have arrested two hunters, John Ebatame and Moses Okoyomon for injuring six persons during a burial. It was gathered that the suspects who are hunters injured the six persons with double barrel gun during an argument over cutting electricity cable with gun shots during the burial ceremony of one late Martina Rabi, in Ama community. Police spokeperson in Edo, SP Kongtongs Bello, has confirmed the incident.